{
  "texts": [
    "This includes stationary desktop computers used at home or in the office, laptops for use while traveling or in meeting rooms, small smartphones that can be used anywhere and are equipped with touch screens, tablets with larger screens than smartphones, smart speakers that can be operated by voice even when hands are not free, and wearable devices like smartwatches that can be carried around and measure heart rate [16].",
    "There exists a wide array of devices for different usage scenarios and purposes.",
    "The services that can be used change significantly even with the same digital device, depending on the availability of a web camera or internet connection.",
    "Moreover, there has been progress in the diversification of user demographics using these services [17,18].",
    "The proliferation of touch screens has made it easier for the elderly and children to operate digital devices."
  ]
}